@startuml
title UC-06 · Serve Packages (Upload side of a UC-02 transfer)
 
participant "Requesting Daemon\n(remote peer's machine,\nrunning its own UC-02)" as RemotePeer
participant "Serving Daemon\n(THIS machine)" as Daemon
participant "pkg cache\n(/var/cache/pkg, read-only)" as Cache
participant Tracker
 
note over RemotePeer, Daemon : Same transfer as UC-02's fetch loop,\nseen from the uploader's side.\npkg is NOT involved anywhere here —\nthis is daemon-to-daemon traffic.
 
RemotePeer -> Daemon: requestPackage(packageName-version)
activate Daemon
 
Daemon -> Daemon : validateRequest()
note right : Network input from an UNTRUSTED\nremote daemon — not user input,\nso not pkg's job. Malformed or\nhostile messages must be rejected\nwithout crashing (fuzzer target,\nper proposal deliverables).
 
Daemon -> Cache: retrieve(packageName-version)
activate Cache
 
alt [package exists locally]
Cache --> Daemon: packageBytes
deactivate Cache
Daemon --> RemotePeer: streamPackageBytes()
note over Daemon, RemotePeer: Requester verifies the hash\non its own end (UC-02).
RemotePeer --> Daemon : transfer complete
 
else [package not found]
Cache --> Daemon: notFound
deactivate Cache
Daemon --> RemotePeer: error("404: package not held")
Daemon -> Tracker: announce(fullPackageList)
note right : Full re-announce (UC-05):\nif one entry drifted, others\nmay have too (e.g. pkg clean).\nDaemon never serves data\nit does not hold.
end
 
deactivate Daemon
@enduml

